The paper describes a natural language comprehension system that uses neural attention to iteratively search for information in text to answer a question. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category, as it specifically covers NLP research. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories, as they cover general AI and ML research. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category, as the paper describes a search process for finding relevant information in text. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible given the use of neural attention in the NLCS.
